<h1>Problem 62 - 2018 Sharygin Q15, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>The altitudes \(AH_1,BH_2,CH_3\) of an acute-angled triangle \(ABC\) meet at point \(H\). Points \(P\) and \(Q\) are the reflections of \(H_2\) and \(H_3\) with respect to \(H\). The circumcircle of triangle \(PH_1Q\) meets for the second time \(BH_2\) and \(CH_3\) at points \(R\) and \(S\). Prove that \(RS\) is a medial line of triangle \(ABC\).</p>
